First you have your ssh private key avble on the git-workstation. 
and you have your ssh pub key on the github server here https://github.com/settings/ssh. 

once you have that just create a repo there in git hub and clone to workstaion. 

clone will not ask any password for sure. 
when adding a file and commit; then push will ask for a password. 

How to authenticate GIT via ssh key

cd /our-repo
cd .git/config

here u can see the url as http:// u have to change this by ssh

change from url = https://github.com/Lforlinux/scripts.git to git@github.com:Lforlinux/scripts.git 
that's it. 
